object:
Holds the local information about contact between 2 bodies
  Contains x and y properties with normalized vector values (from -1 to 1).
For example: `{ y = -1, x = 0 }`

  Table with x and y coordinates of collision.
For example: `{y = 320, x = 480}`
  Indexed array of information about contact points, including normalImpulse, tangentImpulse values and localPoint table for each contact point
  [localNormal] => Table {
             {
               [y] => -1
               [x] => -0
             }
[points] => Table {
             {
               [1] => Table {
                  {
                    [normalImpulse] => 0
                    [localPoint] => Table {
                                {
                                  [y] => 0
                                  [x] => 0
                                }
                    [tangentImpulse] => 0
                  }
             }
[localPoint] => Table {
             {
               [y] => 320.00000953674
               [x] => 480
             }
